qas.question: In the College of Cardinals, the elected Dean needs the approval of who?

plausible_answers.text: The Dean of the College of Cardinals, or Cardinal-dean

qas.question: Who does not need the approval of the Pope?
What is the Dean of the College of Humanities also known as?

plausible_answers.text: Dean of the College of Cardinals, or Cardinal-dean

qas.question: Who does not act as the primus inter pares of the College of Cardinals?

plausible_answers.text: elected by the cardinal bishops holding suburbicarian sees from among their own number, an election, however, that must be approved by the Pope.

qas.question: Who approves the appointment of the Cardinal-dean by the Pope?
What position belonged by right to the shortest-serving of the cardinal bishops?
